A group of killjoy students have proven that Batman's heroic glides through Gotham city wouldn't allow miraculous escapes and flying kicks - instead, Batman would probably die.

To pull off the famous stunt, the Caped Crusader would need a much bigger cape, say a group of British physics students from Leicester - or he should invest in jets to slow his descent.

With his current, smaller cape, Batman would hit the ground at around 50mph, causing catastrophic injuries and probably death.

