In a paper titled ‘Trajectory of a falling Batman’, the group argued that if he jumped from a 492-foot high building, the 15-foot wingspan of Batman's cape would allow him to glide 1148 feet.

However, he would reach a speed of 68 miles per hour before hitting the ground at a life-threatening speed of 50 mph.

